==English==

===Etymology===

From ''macro-'' (large) + ''-fauna'' (animals).

===Noun===

'''macrofauna''' (''plural'' '''macrofaunae''' or '''macrofaunas''')

# A term applied to large [[animals]], not quite large enough to be considered [[megafauna]] but larger than [[microfauna]]. Some include larger species of [[insect]]s and [[annelid]]s in this group.

